"Mary is the symbol of those who made it, but above all those who did not make it, of those who feed the hope of reaching a better place where to root, where to live in full freedom and legality, where the right to childhood is a priority." This was said by the mayor of&nbsp; Lampedusa, Filippo Mannino, during the ceremony of conferring honorary citizenship to the small Maria. In light of the parents' intention to baptize it on the island. Mannino ha&nbsp; added: "This is why our community is in duty and in the right to recognize honorary citizenship, recognition of life, solidarity, respect and protection of human rights of all children who like Mary are born a&nbsp; Lampedusa. The strength of life that breaks into a nightmare scenario, between sea and suffering." &nbsp;

